{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 13:31:46.721002", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview\\n- Topology: 3-tier EBGP Clos (super-spine AS65000, spines AS65100/65101, leaves AS65200/65201), hosts on /24s 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24.\\n- Goal: Assess health, detect anomalies, localize faults, and identify root cause(s).\\n\\nEnd-to-End Reachability\\n- pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: 0% loss, RTT avg 2.186 ms.\\n- pc_0_1 → pc_0_0: 0% loss, RTT avg 3.14 ms.\\n- Assessment: Host-to-host connectivity is healthy with low latency and no loss.\\n\\nControl Plane (BGP) Status\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS65200): 2 eBGP peers (spine_0_0 172.16.0.4, spine_0_1 172.16.0.8), both Established, 1 prefix received from each.\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS65201): 2 eBGP peers (spine_0_0 172.16.0.6, spine_0_1 172.16.0.10), both Established, 1 prefix received from each.\\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS65100): 3 eBGP peers (super-spine 172.16.0.0, leaves 172.16.0.5/0.7), all Established. PfxRcd: 0 from super-spine, 1 from each leaf.\\n- spine_router_0_1 (AS65101): 3 eBGP peers (super-spine 172.16.0.2, leaves 172.16.0.9/0.11), all Established. PfxRcd: 2 from super-spine, 2 from each leaf.\\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS65000): 2 eBGP peers (spine_0_0 172.16.0.1, spine_0_1 172.16.0.3), both Established. PfxRcd: 2 from each spine.\\n\\nData Plane (Routing) Snapshot\\n- leaf_router_0_0: Connected 10.0.0.0/24; BGP route to 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.4 (spine_0_0).\\n- leaf_router_0_1: Connected 10.0.1.0/24; BGP route to 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6 (spine_0_0).\\n- spine_router_0_0: BGP routes to 10.0.0.0/24 via leaf_0_0 and 10.0.1.0/24 via leaf_0_1.\\n- spine_router_0_1: BGP routes to 10.0.0.0/24 via leaf_0_0 and 10.0.1.0/24 via leaf_0_1.\\n- super_spine_router_0: BGP routes to both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 via spine_router_0_0 (single best-path selected).\\n\\nFindings and Assessment\\n1) End-to-end health: Normal\\n- Bidirectional host reachability without loss or abnormal latency.\\n\\n2) BGP adjacencies: Normal\\n- All eBGP sessions are Established across leaves, spines, and super-spine.\\n\\n3) Route propagation and selection: Normal with expected asymmetries\\n- Super-spine learns both leaf prefixes from both spines but currently selects spine_router_0_0 as best-path for both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24.\\n- spine_router_0_0 shows 0 accepted prefixes from super-spine; spine_router_0_1 shows 2. This asymmetry is expected:\\n  - When super-spine’s best path to both prefixes is via spine_router_0_0, advertisements back toward spine_router_0_0 include AS65100 in the AS_PATH. spine_router_0_0 rejects these routes due to AS-path loop prevention (self-AS present).\\n  - spine_router_0_1 accepts the super-spine’s best paths (its AS is not in the AS_PATH for those), hence PfxRcd=2.\\n- Leaves each learn the remote /24 via a single spine (no ECMP in use), which is consistent with typical default EBGP behavior without maximum-paths configured.\\n\\nAnomalies Detected\\n- No functional anomalies impacting connectivity or routing correctness were observed.\\n- Note: The observed lack of ECMP and asymmetric PfxRcd between spines and super-spine are consistent with standard EBGP best-path selection and AS-path loop prevention; they do not indicate a fault.\\n\\nLocalization and Root Cause\\n- Faulty devices: None identified.\\n- Root cause for observed asymmetry: EBGP best-path selection at the super-spine combined with AS-path loop prevention at the spines, leading to one spine accepting 0 prefixes from the super-spine while the other accepts 2. This is expected behavior, not an error.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- The network is operating normally: all BGP sessions up, routes present and consistent, and hosts can communicate without loss.\\n- No corrective actions are indicated based on the current state., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='e3ac34fc-a4bf-4883-837c-76ee9c21dd3a'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
